{
  "name": "RPlog_In_the_Atrium",
  "title": "A Water Flute in the University Atrium",
  "summary": "In the dark, glowbug-lit atrium of the University of Corellia, the Jedi student and mechanic Orson Tighe sits in meditation, playing a mournful improvised tune on a water flute that deepens his connection to the Force. His teacher Jessalyn, weary and feeling alone after the loss of Simon and her growing distance from Luke, seeks him out and joins him in the grass. The two share a quiet, searching conversation about whether the Jedi path leads only to tragedy, and whether there is value in finding peace and rest in one's own life rather than running forever toward some resolution. Jessalyn confesses her longing for love, family, and an end to wielding a lightsaber, and asks Orson to give Luke Skywalker a chance despite their conflict, which he agrees to do. As night falls and Orson gently calls a curious little animal from the brush, he reaffirms his commitment to becoming a Jedi before gathering his books and departing without a spoken goodbye, his presence still lingering through the Force.",
